        "title": "Convert MySQL db to embeddable database for Java jdbc",
        "body": "<p>Before I created a project which is a huge system, I didn't know that <code>Mysql<\/code> database can't be embedded to a project in Java created in <strong>Netbeans<\/strong>.<\/p>\n\n<p>What I did was to add <code>Mysql Connector J<\/code> <strong>jar<\/strong> file to my project then I used <strong>Mysql Workbench IDE<\/strong> to manage and create the database and objects such as the stored procedures.<\/p>\n\n<p>The database is now contained in <strong>Mysql Workbench<\/strong> which is outside of the Netbeans project. <\/p>\n\n<p>I have a huge project and 40-50s of stored procedures(used as <code>CallableStatements<\/code> in project), about 20 or more tables. <\/p>\n\n<p>Eventually when project is complete and ready, I think I will need to embed the database together with the project (which I haven't done in the past).<\/p>\n\n<p>I don't know how I can possibly solve this because I don't want to rewrite the tables and stored procedures from scratch if I use a different database such as <code>Derby<\/code> and <code>H2<\/code>. <\/p>\n\n<p>Also, the reason I used the <strong>MySQL Workbench<\/strong> is to have a GUI for viewing my tables and its properties.<\/p>\n\n<p>By the way the project is a desktop application done in <code>Swing<\/code>.<\/p>\n\n<p>What is the best action and solution that you can advise?<\/p>\n\n<p>I hope you can help.<\/p>\n\n<p>Thanks.<\/p>\n",
        "question_id": 41318738,
